.TH db_pt  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBdb_pt\fR \-  Returns the X or Y coordinate of any point
.SH Syntax  \fBdb_pt\fR  {-x | -y}   <pt>  [-help] 
.P Returns the X or Y coordinate of any point. When you need to find the coordinates of a shape in order to either move the shape or change a coordinate of a shape, the command helps you find the coordinates. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB{-x | -y}            \fR" Returns the coordinates of the points.
.RS  "*" 2 -x returns x
.RE
.RS  "*" 2 -y returns y
.RE   "\fBpt\fR" Specifies the point to access the value from. This is a mandatory parameter.   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each db_pt parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all its parameters, use the man command:  man db_pt 
.SH Example
.RS  "*" 2 db_pt -x {10.1 11.1} returns 10.1
.RE
.RS  "*" 2 db_pt -y {10.1 11.1} returns 11.1  "*" 2 db_pt 10.1 11.2 -y returns 11.2 
.RE 
.SH Related Information
.P db_rect
.P
